In the intricate dance of nature, the dietary preferences of herbivores like deer often intertwine with the botanical characteristics of plants, leading to a fascinating interplay of survival strategies. Succulent plants, renowned for their water-retaining properties and thick, fleshy leaves, stand as a distinctive group in this dynamic ecosystem. Exploring the relationship between deer and succulents unveils a nuanced narrative of selective feeding behavior and adaptive mechanisms.

